1
00:00:36,662 --> 00:00:40,082
<i>You need to know from the get-go,
this is about nothing.</i>

2
00:00:40,250 --> 00:00:42,543
<i>Just a geometrical contradiction.</i>

3
00:00:44,128 --> 00:00:47,215
<i>The story of a dumb, round planet
revolving aimlessly</i>

4
00:00:47,381 --> 00:00:50,969
<i>around a dumb, round sun
burning aimlessly.</i>

5
00:00:52,052 --> 00:00:53,345
<i>The story of a round belly</i>

6
00:00:53,554 --> 00:00:56,640
<i>purposefully containing
a round, gooey thing.</i>

7
00:00:57,100 --> 00:00:58,976
<i>That becomes an un-gooey thing.</i>

8
00:00:59,226 --> 00:01:01,353
<i>That looks at lots of round things.</i>

9
00:01:01,979 --> 00:01:03,523
<i>The rounds of freedom.</i>

10
00:01:04,649 --> 00:01:05,567
<i>Sophie's round dots.</i>

11
00:01:07,819 --> 00:01:09,445
<i>Samantha's round rounds.</i>

12
00:01:10,028 --> 00:01:12,198
<i>As round as people's round glasses.</i>

13
00:01:13,115 --> 00:01:13,908
<i>Round.</i>

14
00:01:20,206 --> 00:01:22,667
<i>It's also the tale
of a curve going straight</i>

15
00:01:22,917 --> 00:01:25,043
<i>and becoming a rigid angle.</i>

16
00:01:25,837 --> 00:01:28,631
<i>A square squishing a round
with the rule book.</i>

17
00:01:29,466 --> 00:01:31,216
<i>A squared-off morality tale.</i>

18
00:01:33,177 --> 00:01:34,679
<i>Square education.</i>

19
00:01:36,305 --> 00:01:38,348
<i>Like square food at school,</i>

20
00:01:38,515 --> 00:01:40,018
<i>college, university...</i>

21
00:01:40,602 --> 00:01:41,728
<i>Square to the jaw like...</i>

22
00:01:41,895 --> 00:01:42,561
It's over!

23
00:01:43,688 --> 00:01:45,899
<i>As square as square people's glasses.</i>

24
00:01:46,064 --> 00:01:46,983
Here we go.

25
00:01:47,859 --> 00:01:48,817
<i>Square games.</i>

26
00:01:50,110 --> 00:01:51,695
<i>Square office life.</i>

27
00:01:52,739 --> 00:01:54,656
<i>Square. Like your father's cancer.</i>

28
00:01:55,073 --> 00:01:55,866
<i>Square.</i>

29
00:01:57,201 --> 00:02:00,245
<i>So we come to the contradictory aspect
of our story.</i>

30
00:02:00,412 --> 00:02:02,873
<i>Of the few things we can be sure of,</i>

31
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:06,543
<i>there is one even the worst skeptics
cannot call into question.</i>

32
00:02:09,046 --> 00:02:11,674
<i>A square peg never fits in a round hole.</i>

33
00:02:13,634 --> 00:02:14,718
<i>Never.</i>

34
00:02:17,222 --> 00:02:18,598
<i>And vice-versa.</i>

35
00:03:11,943 --> 00:03:13,360
Morning, everybody.

36
00:03:13,569 --> 00:03:14,903
Morning.

37
00:03:20,701 --> 00:03:22,495
What about your cortisone?

38
00:03:22,662 --> 00:03:24,288
I stopped. I get so bloated.

39
00:03:24,454 --> 00:03:27,165
But it stops you sleeping all day.

40
00:03:27,332 --> 00:03:29,586
Rest assured, honey, you're already fat.

41
00:03:29,752 --> 00:03:33,840
You can bloat all you want,
it's like tennis socks in boots.

42
00:03:34,007 --> 00:03:35,174
Nobody will notice.

43
00:03:36,216 --> 00:03:37,301
I'll take it.

44
00:03:38,010 --> 00:03:39,762
What's on the agenda today?

45
00:03:39,929 --> 00:03:42,307
Playing Candy Crush on the couch.

46
00:03:42,807 --> 00:03:45,727
No, not playing Candy Crush
on the couch.

47
00:03:45,894 --> 00:03:48,937
I have my meeting with HR
this afternoon.

48
00:03:49,104 --> 00:03:50,564
- It's today?
- At 3.

49
00:03:50,731 --> 00:03:53,484
Six months waiting
and you sit on it all weekend?

50
00:03:53,735 --> 00:03:54,401
I forgot it.

51
00:03:54,569 --> 00:03:56,236
- Forgot?
- I didn't think.

52
00:03:58,906 --> 00:04:00,991
I didn't want to think about it.

53
00:04:08,540 --> 00:04:10,126
Come on, kids, let's go.

54
00:04:12,753 --> 00:04:14,046
Have a good day, son.

55
00:04:14,212 --> 00:04:15,340
I wanna die.

56
00:04:15,506 --> 00:04:18,550
Obviously. It's your acne.
You'll be over it by lunch.

57
00:04:19,843 --> 00:04:20,637
I hate you.

58
00:04:22,930 --> 00:04:24,182
Obviously, too.

59
00:04:33,191 --> 00:04:34,108
You good?

60
00:04:40,740 --> 00:04:42,033
Let's go!

61
00:05:05,807 --> 00:05:06,723
It doesn't matter.

62
00:05:06,891 --> 00:05:07,850
Stuff happens.

63
00:05:09,143 --> 00:05:11,144
Maybe it was too early.

64
00:05:12,230 --> 00:05:13,605
No? I don't know.

65
00:05:14,774 --> 00:05:16,149
What do you think?

66
00:05:42,759 --> 00:05:46,930
SINK OR SWIM

67
00:06:50,620 --> 00:06:51,454
One.

68
00:06:51,704 --> 00:06:52,288
Two.

69
00:06:52,454 --> 00:06:54,290
Grace. Elegance.

70
00:06:54,456 --> 00:06:58,043
Five, six, seven, eight!

71
00:07:06,927 --> 00:07:08,428
We can go, I'm ready.

72
00:07:25,822 --> 00:07:29,658
<i>Swimmer wanted to join
men's synchronized swim team.</i>

73
00:07:29,826 --> 00:07:31,536
<i>Amateurs welcome.</i>

74
00:07:35,122 --> 00:07:37,375
The teacher said I didn't talk.

75
00:07:37,542 --> 00:07:39,627
After, I did somersaults.

76
00:07:39,793 --> 00:07:41,254
It was really good.

77
00:07:41,420 --> 00:07:42,838
And flips and things.

78
00:07:43,004 --> 00:07:46,091
The teacher said I had to leave class...

79
00:07:52,682 --> 00:07:56,894
There's no federation,
league or whatever.

80
00:07:57,185 --> 00:08:00,148
I guess we could start one
if we write letters

81
00:08:00,314 --> 00:08:02,524
to someone somewhere.

82
00:08:02,692 --> 00:08:04,485
We never discussed it much

83
00:08:04,651 --> 00:08:06,946
'cause we don't give a damn.

84
00:08:07,697 --> 00:08:12,160
Practice times depend on school days
and the water polo club.

85
00:08:12,326 --> 00:08:14,411
Mondays, it's at 6:30.

86
00:08:14,579 --> 00:08:15,913
Thursdays at 7,

87
00:08:16,079 --> 00:08:19,917
but you can arrive
ten minutes later if you want.

88
00:08:20,084 --> 00:08:21,377
It's no problem.

89
00:08:21,543 --> 00:08:23,670
We do it for fun, after all.

90
00:08:23,838 --> 00:08:25,298
It's not the army.

91
00:08:25,714 --> 00:08:27,466
It's just a little...

92
00:08:29,927 --> 00:08:32,429
I'm Thierry
but you can call me Titi.

93
00:08:32,721 --> 00:08:34,264
No, Thierry's fine.

94
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:37,434
I don't know why I said that.
Nobody calls me Titi.

95
00:08:37,601 --> 00:08:39,812
It's like, you big boob, right?

96
00:08:40,020 --> 00:08:41,355
Yes, for sure.

97
00:08:42,606 --> 00:08:46,610
I'm thrilled you answered the ad.
You'll see, we're one big family.

98
00:08:46,777 --> 00:08:49,529
Not a real family, but kind of.

99
00:08:50,239 --> 00:08:51,407
Welcome!

100
00:08:53,658 --> 00:08:54,744
Guys!

101
00:08:55,494 --> 00:08:57,705
Guys! This is Bertrand.

102
00:08:58,246 --> 00:08:59,498
Hi, Bertrand.

103
00:09:00,374 --> 00:09:02,375
Everybody in the pool.

104
00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:12,010
Delphine!

105
00:09:12,177 --> 00:09:14,846
This is Bertrand.
He called about the ad!

106
00:09:19,518 --> 00:09:20,894
So what brings you here?

107
00:09:21,062 --> 00:09:22,687
I don't really know.

108
00:09:23,648 --> 00:09:24,649
You don't know?

109
00:09:24,941 --> 00:09:26,192
You know what we do?

110
00:09:26,359 --> 00:09:29,695
Yes, sure.
Synchronized swimming for men.

111
00:09:29,861 --> 00:09:32,240
What is synchronized swimming for men?

112
00:09:32,782 --> 00:09:34,825
The same as for women, I guess.

113
00:09:34,991 --> 00:09:35,993
But for men.

114
00:09:36,494 --> 00:09:39,246
- It made you want to sign up?
- Not exactly.

115
00:09:40,331 --> 00:09:41,957
So what the hell brings you here?

116
00:09:42,124 --> 00:09:44,125
Guys, it's called training!

117
00:09:46,461 --> 00:09:48,255
Men's synchronized swimming

118
00:09:48,422 --> 00:09:50,216
is not for everybody.

119
00:09:50,383 --> 00:09:52,176
Many are called, few are chosen.

120
00:09:52,342 --> 00:09:53,677
The guys you see here

121
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:55,721
aren't here by chance.

122
00:09:55,888 --> 00:09:57,139
They want it.

123
00:09:58,139 --> 00:10:00,142
To make this team, Bertrand,

124
00:10:00,518 --> 00:10:03,019
you must combine willpower,
grace, rhythm

125
00:10:03,187 --> 00:10:04,772
and a healthy lifestyle.

126
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:06,274
Can you cut it?

127
00:10:08,484 --> 00:10:11,528
- You can swim at least?
- Sure. Quite well.

128
00:10:12,488 --> 00:10:13,739
I don't know.

129
00:10:15,490 --> 00:10:17,033
You know nothing, in fact.

130
00:10:18,244 --> 00:10:19,327
Not anymore.

131
00:10:21,288 --> 00:10:23,081
Great, you made the team.

132
00:10:25,083 --> 00:10:26,126
Move! Locker room!

133
00:10:26,293 --> 00:10:30,213
Grab trunks, cap, nose clip, goggles.
In the pool in 5!

134
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:32,508
Now that's a warm welcome.

135
00:10:32,674 --> 00:10:33,884
Run along!

136
00:10:40,725 --> 00:10:42,350
"What, no treason?

137
00:10:42,643 --> 00:10:44,352
"This grief is without reason.

138
00:10:45,687 --> 00:10:47,315
"It is indeed the worst pain

139
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:49,024
"Not to know why

140
00:10:50,359 --> 00:10:53,236
"Without love, without hate
My heart suffers this fate."

141
00:10:54,488 --> 00:10:55,697
Let's go again.

142
00:11:03,706 --> 00:11:06,792
"Sweet sound of rain
On the earth and roofs

143
00:11:07,460 --> 00:11:08,918
"For a heart that wanes

144
00:11:09,169 --> 00:11:10,962
"Sweet is the song of rain!"

145
00:11:12,423 --> 00:11:14,674
Knock it off now!

146
00:11:15,634 --> 00:11:17,802
Pain in the ass! You all piss me off!

147
00:11:21,599 --> 00:11:24,434
I didn't drive 40 minutes here for this!

148
00:11:25,477 --> 00:11:27,062
I want to train!

149
00:11:28,063 --> 00:11:30,482
Look at you! What the hell!

150
00:11:31,359 --> 00:11:32,817
I want discipline!

151
00:11:33,402 --> 00:11:34,611
I'm sick of it!

152
00:11:36,529 --> 00:11:38,865
Very well, let's go again.

153
00:12:02,972 --> 00:12:06,476
They made me do tests
like it was for a space flight.

154
00:12:06,644 --> 00:12:09,772
Cholesterol level,
this level, that level.

155
00:12:09,938 --> 00:12:12,066
Whatever. Two days it took,

156
00:12:12,232 --> 00:12:14,735
only for them to send a letter saying,

157
00:12:14,943 --> 00:12:16,778
I'm in super shape.

158
00:12:16,946 --> 00:12:19,532
But I'm too old to get a mortgage.

159
00:12:22,076 --> 00:12:23,701
38, and I'm too old.

160
00:12:23,869 --> 00:12:24,953
It's absurd.

161
00:12:27,163 --> 00:12:28,999
Now I keep obsessing about it.

162
00:12:30,292 --> 00:12:32,419
I look at myself in the mirror

163
00:12:33,546 --> 00:12:35,004
and find wrinkles.

164
00:12:35,630 --> 00:12:37,341
I'm easily out of breath.

165
00:12:38,134 --> 00:12:39,259
38 years old.

166
00:12:40,677 --> 00:12:42,971
All because I wanted to buy a place.

167
00:12:43,847 --> 00:12:46,142
I don't know
if you guys own your homes.

168
00:12:46,892 --> 00:12:49,394
But I'm telling you, rent!

169
00:12:50,895 --> 00:12:52,440
Save on metaphysical shooot.

170
00:12:58,736 --> 00:12:59,738
I appreciate it.

171
00:13:16,922 --> 00:13:18,506
- Morning, boss.
- Morning.

172
00:13:50,914 --> 00:13:53,667
You're up bright and early.
What are you doing?

173
00:13:53,834 --> 00:13:55,711
Eating my apple turnover.

174
00:13:57,629 --> 00:13:58,630
Say, Nicolas,

175
00:13:58,797 --> 00:14:00,924
we open the store at 10.

176
00:14:01,966 --> 00:14:03,052
Not 10:30.

177
00:14:03,510 --> 00:14:04,928
- We open at 10:30.
- Don't.

178
00:14:05,095 --> 00:14:06,138
- We do.
- Don't.

179
00:14:06,304 --> 00:14:07,222
- Do!
- Don't!

180
00:14:07,639 --> 00:14:09,140
It says so on the door!

181
00:14:09,350 --> 00:14:12,269
It means 10 o'clock here.
10:30, ready to sell.

182
00:14:12,519 --> 00:14:14,855
You arrive at 10:30 and then what?

183
00:14:15,022 --> 00:14:17,399
Get a coffee,
check email and stuff.

184
00:14:17,566 --> 00:14:19,400
That takes us to 11:30.

185
00:14:19,610 --> 00:14:21,236
Meanwhile, folks come by,

186
00:14:21,403 --> 00:14:22,863
looking for a pool.

187
00:14:23,029 --> 00:14:24,322
These pools don't sell.

188
00:14:24,490 --> 00:14:26,658
They don't sell, I lose money on them.

189
00:14:26,825 --> 00:14:28,536
Nobody buys mine in the end.

190
00:14:29,537 --> 00:14:31,371
Even afternoons are quiet.

191
00:14:31,871 --> 00:14:32,873
Yes but...

192
00:14:34,124 --> 00:14:36,543
I can talk like a boss sometimes, right?

193
00:14:40,172 --> 00:14:41,548
Do you have any weed?

194
00:14:52,559 --> 00:14:55,229
- It's me.
<i>- Two hours she's been waiting.</i>

195
00:14:55,395 --> 00:14:57,898
I know, sorry. This guy...

196
00:14:58,481 --> 00:14:59,524
<i>She's coming down.</i>

197
00:14:59,692 --> 00:15:02,235
- All good?
<i>- Wonderful. Lola's on her way.</i>

198
00:15:06,615 --> 00:15:07,323
Scissors.

199
00:15:07,490 --> 00:15:11,452
Don't hold back.
Express yourself through the whole word.

200
00:15:12,288 --> 00:15:13,205
Phyllo.

201
00:15:14,163 --> 00:15:14,873
Good.

202
00:15:16,332 --> 00:15:17,250
Banjo.

203
00:15:32,850 --> 00:15:34,309
Your son is hindered.

204
00:15:34,475 --> 00:15:36,352
He has a real mental blockage.

205
00:15:36,894 --> 00:15:39,565
Communication between you is crucial.

206
00:15:39,731 --> 00:15:41,774
Involve him, stimulate him.

207
00:15:42,442 --> 00:15:43,860
Maybe drama classes or...

208
00:15:44,611 --> 00:15:46,447
Excuse me, are you a shrink?

209
00:15:46,739 --> 00:15:48,032
No, you're not a shrink.

210
00:15:48,197 --> 00:15:52,452
So we'll stop there.
I don't pay you for a parenting lesson.

211
00:15:52,620 --> 00:15:54,580
Just do your job, that's plenty.

212
00:16:04,756 --> 00:16:06,216
Seventy-six!

213
00:16:13,765 --> 00:16:16,644
- How are you feeling, champ?
- Copacetic.

214
00:16:16,851 --> 00:16:18,102
They're rocking.

215
00:16:18,854 --> 00:16:19,812
Not quite rocking.

216
00:16:19,980 --> 00:16:20,938
Simon!

217
00:16:21,148 --> 00:16:24,234
You're on after the bingo.
5-6 minutes, tops.

218
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:25,568
When I do this...

219
00:16:29,072 --> 00:16:31,200
Has he got nerve issues?

220
00:17:11,155 --> 00:17:12,907
So how was the party?

221
00:17:13,075 --> 00:17:14,492
A lot of people turned up?

222
00:17:19,707 --> 00:17:21,208
I wish I'd been there.

223
00:17:38,683 --> 00:17:40,352
Here. Forty for you.

224
00:17:40,769 --> 00:17:43,605
The blue spot during the intro,
did it dazzle you?

225
00:17:43,771 --> 00:17:45,065
I could hardly see.

226
00:17:45,231 --> 00:17:48,861
I'll try it behind.
Like you step out of a flying saucer.

227
00:17:49,486 --> 00:17:50,403
Mauve then.

228
00:17:50,570 --> 00:17:51,572
Mauve, sure.

229
00:17:52,698 --> 00:17:54,074
Are you guys for real?

230
00:18:28,692 --> 00:18:29,777
Take it easy!

231
00:18:31,194 --> 00:18:32,320
What?

232
00:18:32,488 --> 00:18:35,031
Third time this month
we've moved you on, sir.

233
00:18:35,324 --> 00:18:38,035
We've played nice so far. Now beat it.

234
00:18:38,660 --> 00:18:41,246
This isn't for camping,
it's for parking.

235
00:18:41,413 --> 00:18:42,372
OK, we're going.

236
00:18:42,538 --> 00:18:43,999
- Right now.
- Sure.

237
00:18:48,961 --> 00:18:50,463
They woke you up.

238
00:18:52,883 --> 00:18:54,259
I'm going, dad.

239
00:18:54,843 --> 00:18:56,636
Already? Without breakfast?

240
00:18:56,804 --> 00:18:58,012
I'm not hungry.

241
00:18:59,263 --> 00:19:01,224
I thought we'd spend the day together

242
00:19:01,391 --> 00:19:03,143
and I'd drop you at mom's tonight.

243
00:19:04,102 --> 00:19:05,729
It's your call but it's...

244
00:19:11,777 --> 00:19:13,737
You didn't say, how was my gig?

245
00:19:53,527 --> 00:19:54,819
And stretch.

246
00:19:55,278 --> 00:19:56,320
What's stretching?

247
00:19:56,488 --> 00:19:58,030
No, look, you're...

248
00:19:58,240 --> 00:20:00,576
Too tight, too stiff. All wrong.

249
00:20:00,741 --> 00:20:03,202
So scared of looking stupid,
you almost do.

250
00:20:04,078 --> 00:20:05,663
Listening is crucial.

251
00:20:05,873 --> 00:20:09,041
You need music in you
to make the world dance.

252
00:20:09,209 --> 00:20:10,167
Stretch....

253
00:20:10,335 --> 00:20:11,586
Mermaids, yes!

254
00:20:12,421 --> 00:20:15,548
Let's find our inner woman.

255
00:20:16,258 --> 00:20:17,843
I don't have an inner woman.

256
00:20:18,009 --> 00:20:21,930
Bullshit. Finding her
might help you grow a pair.

257
00:20:22,597 --> 00:20:24,223
I know I don't have one.

258
00:20:25,224 --> 00:20:27,435
Reach up and stretch. Ballerinas!

259
00:20:27,728 --> 00:20:28,729
Ballerina!

260
00:20:29,270 --> 00:20:30,814
Let's find some grace.

261
00:20:31,147 --> 00:20:32,900
It's in there somewhere.

262
00:20:33,733 --> 00:20:37,445
Remember, we have a show coming up,
so let's be ready. Let's go!

263
00:20:37,613 --> 00:20:39,364
Sorry, you're not in the gala.

264
00:20:39,698 --> 00:20:40,907
You're not up to it.

265
00:20:41,074 --> 00:20:41,909
Yeah.

266
00:20:43,618 --> 00:20:46,246
He says, you'll see, it's an easy climb.

267
00:20:46,413 --> 00:20:49,082
But I can see it's no easy climb.

268
00:20:49,249 --> 00:20:51,710
So I say, watch out, I'm no...

269
00:20:52,169 --> 00:20:53,502
I'm no mountaineer.

270
00:20:53,670 --> 00:20:55,047
I hike for fun.

271
00:20:55,212 --> 00:20:56,173
An amateur.

272
00:20:56,381 --> 00:21:00,009
Simply to keep him company
and my auntie happy.

273
00:21:00,176 --> 00:21:01,385
He's my stepfather.

274
00:21:02,511 --> 00:21:05,682
He says, no, don't worry.

275
00:21:06,098 --> 00:21:07,517
He insists.

276
00:21:08,393 --> 00:21:11,395
I didn't follow him,
I stayed down below.

277
00:21:13,356 --> 00:21:14,273
Is that it?

278
00:21:14,857 --> 00:21:16,984
It really wasn't very interesting.

279
00:21:17,736 --> 00:21:19,528
You say that 'cause it's Thierry?

280
00:21:20,071 --> 00:21:22,031
I thought we agreed not to judge.

281
00:21:22,240 --> 00:21:23,157
No judging, OK?

282
00:21:23,325 --> 00:21:25,661
That's the rule.
Without rules, I'm gone.

283
00:21:25,826 --> 00:21:28,163
He's right.
If we're judged, we won't talk.

284
00:21:28,329 --> 00:21:30,958
Sorry but what he says
is always kinda weird.

285
00:21:31,458 --> 00:21:32,500
That's my point.

286
00:21:32,667 --> 00:21:35,378
No, thanks.
On anti-depressants, I can't.

287
00:21:40,925 --> 00:21:42,635
I'm in depression.

288
00:21:46,347 --> 00:21:47,974
A major depression.

289
00:21:53,313 --> 00:21:55,565
I don't really know where to begin.

290
00:21:59,987 --> 00:22:02,864
Two years now, I've been off work.

291
00:22:07,786 --> 00:22:09,078
So long, guys!

292
00:22:12,582 --> 00:22:13,834
See you, Simon.

293
00:22:51,246 --> 00:22:52,288
flap!

294
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:54,249
flaping shooot!

295
00:22:55,666 --> 00:22:56,542
Claire?

296
00:22:57,001 --> 00:22:59,296
Is there any brandy for Thibault?

297
00:22:59,462 --> 00:23:00,297
There.

298
00:23:07,179 --> 00:23:10,347
Take it from me,
this country's going to hell.

299
00:23:11,057 --> 00:23:13,477
I see it at work every day. Believe me.

300
00:23:13,852 --> 00:23:15,269
People have no respect.

301
00:23:19,691 --> 00:23:21,151
You're very quiet, Bertrand.

302
00:23:21,567 --> 00:23:22,611
All good?

303
00:23:23,987 --> 00:23:24,904
Great.

304
00:23:26,490 --> 00:23:27,199
Better.

305
00:23:27,615 --> 00:23:28,657
No, good.

306
00:23:28,909 --> 00:23:30,701
Claire said you do sports.

307
00:23:31,077 --> 00:23:32,496
That's good. Great!

308
00:23:34,247 --> 00:23:35,624
What kind of sport?

309
00:23:36,083 --> 00:23:37,584
I signed up for a...

310
00:23:38,167 --> 00:23:40,921
A swim team. Synchronized swimming.

311
00:23:41,212 --> 00:23:42,756
Remind me what that is.

312
00:23:43,006 --> 00:23:44,924
Like in those 50s movies?

313
00:23:47,635 --> 00:23:48,720
Water ballet?

314
00:23:48,929 --> 00:23:49,762
That's right.

315
00:23:49,930 --> 00:23:51,097
Isn't it for...

316
00:23:51,556 --> 00:23:52,348
I mean, it's...

317
00:23:52,516 --> 00:23:54,017
For women? Sure.

318
00:23:54,476 --> 00:23:55,602
I'm sorry.

319
00:23:56,603 --> 00:23:58,771
- But this is for men.
- Great.

320
00:24:00,272 --> 00:24:02,108
After all, women play soccer.

321
00:24:05,528 --> 00:24:08,155
My offer of a job at the store
is still open.

322
00:24:10,075 --> 00:24:11,451
Thanks, I appreciate it.

323
00:24:12,160 --> 00:24:13,702
It's no big deal.

324
00:24:15,163 --> 00:24:16,789
When did you last get away?

325
00:24:17,164 --> 00:24:18,791
Ever since Bertrand....

326
00:24:21,044 --> 00:24:22,837
What's that? Two years?

327
00:24:23,838 --> 00:24:25,257
Something like that.

328
00:24:26,340 --> 00:24:28,718
Two years is a lot, don't you think?

329
00:24:29,885 --> 00:24:30,929
I mean,

330
00:24:31,346 --> 00:24:33,056
six months, a year maybe.

331
00:24:33,222 --> 00:24:34,223
But two years!

332
00:24:34,391 --> 00:24:36,101
Sure, but it's two years. Period.

333
00:24:36,268 --> 00:24:38,979
Nothing against Bertrand.
I love the guy.

334
00:24:40,188 --> 00:24:41,690
I'm worried, that's all.

335
00:24:42,398 --> 00:24:43,567
I know.

336
00:24:48,613 --> 00:24:50,531
My little darling sister.

337
00:24:59,583 --> 00:25:00,625
Bye!

338
00:25:01,084 --> 00:25:02,501
Remind me, never again.

339
00:25:02,669 --> 00:25:04,712
15 years I've been reminding you.

340
00:25:09,968 --> 00:25:11,760
That's horrible. I'm horrible.

341
00:25:12,429 --> 00:25:14,806
It's not normal
to have these thoughts.

342
00:25:15,182 --> 00:25:15,932
What thoughts?

343
00:25:16,098 --> 00:25:18,727
I had an atrocious vision in my mind...

344
00:25:19,269 --> 00:25:20,353
A comet?

345
00:25:20,519 --> 00:25:21,855
How do you know?

346
00:25:22,063 --> 00:25:23,480
I had the same vision.

347
00:25:23,940 --> 00:25:26,358
I saw a glimmer in the sky,
like a star,

348
00:25:26,526 --> 00:25:28,444
but it was blue, red, green.

349
00:25:28,612 --> 00:25:32,574
It's alive, headed for us,
dazzling, about to flatten us but...

350
00:25:33,657 --> 00:25:35,535
It slams into your sister's BMW.

351
00:25:35,701 --> 00:25:37,537
Explosions, screams, flames!

352
00:25:37,828 --> 00:25:39,330
All dead!

353
00:25:40,248 --> 00:25:41,458
Atrocious.

354
00:25:44,336 --> 00:25:45,420
I'm cold.

355
00:25:45,586 --> 00:25:46,962
Let's go to bed.

356
00:25:52,635 --> 00:25:54,011
Time, guys!

357
00:25:56,513 --> 00:25:58,557
I know I'm a party pooper. Be cool.

358
00:25:59,017 --> 00:26:02,519
I'm the one getting his knuckles
rapped by city hall.

359
00:26:02,811 --> 00:26:04,940
9 o'clock does not mean 9:30.

360
00:26:06,232 --> 00:26:10,028
If you want to stay later,
ask for permission.

361
00:26:10,945 --> 00:26:12,071
Or go talk outside.

362
00:26:16,159 --> 00:26:17,285
That's nonsense!

363
00:27:09,378 --> 00:27:12,840
It's a thrill to see
so many of you here

364
00:27:13,008 --> 00:27:16,970
for the fourth round
of the Interregional Water Polo Cup!

365
00:27:19,221 --> 00:27:22,182
We have a water-themed
curtain-raiser for you.

366
00:27:22,642 --> 00:27:24,810
They're nervous
before their first ever show.

367
00:27:25,769 --> 00:27:27,439
Let's give a big hand

368
00:27:27,980 --> 00:27:31,526
for our first
synchronized swim team for men.

369
00:27:31,734 --> 00:27:33,193
That's right, for men!

370
00:27:33,361 --> 00:27:34,278
Give it up!

371
00:28:05,226 --> 00:28:06,560
That's your team?

372
00:28:35,673 --> 00:28:36,883
Magnificent!

373
00:28:58,404 --> 00:28:59,905
Let's hear it for them!

374
00:29:02,741 --> 00:29:05,994
Never an easy discipline,
synchronized swimming.

375
00:29:08,623 --> 00:29:10,416
Time now for the ball game!

376
00:29:10,666 --> 00:29:12,042
Time for some water polo!

377
00:29:12,210 --> 00:29:14,461
Our fourth-round match

378
00:29:14,962 --> 00:29:16,297
between Jugnac

379
00:29:16,964 --> 00:29:18,799
and Chevigny-Le-Ouin.

380
00:29:30,979 --> 00:29:32,396
Team mates forever!

381
00:29:32,564 --> 00:29:34,065
I'm so proud of you.

382
00:29:35,023 --> 00:29:36,025
Bravo!

383
00:29:37,652 --> 00:29:38,694
It was...

384
00:29:38,862 --> 00:29:40,738
Bravo for what? We were shooot.

385
00:29:41,614 --> 00:29:43,700
Look at them. Like they won the cup.

386
00:29:44,159 --> 00:29:45,410
They're having fun.

387
00:29:45,576 --> 00:29:46,743
They look happy.

388
00:29:47,202 --> 00:29:48,621
Sure, they look happy.

389
00:29:49,413 --> 00:29:51,039
Looking isn't being.

390
00:29:53,250 --> 00:29:55,920
Sounds like
someone's more depressed than me.

391
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:05,387
Our first performance. It was insane.
The crowd went wild.

392
00:30:05,555 --> 00:30:07,932
I'm super proud of the guys.

393
00:30:08,557 --> 00:30:11,810
I just wanted to tell you.
Love you, bye.

394
00:30:13,855 --> 00:30:14,897
Guys...

395
00:30:15,355 --> 00:30:17,275
I gotta go or he'll go crazy.

396
00:30:17,442 --> 00:30:18,317
- Sure?
- Yeah.

397
00:30:18,484 --> 00:30:21,153
- Thanks, Delphine.
- See you. You were great!

398
00:30:24,531 --> 00:30:26,867
I'll be going too. Need a ride?

399
00:30:27,285 --> 00:30:28,286
With pleasure.

400
00:30:39,338 --> 00:30:41,007
I've released seventeen CDs.

401
00:30:41,673 --> 00:30:43,425
More or less self-produced.

402
00:30:43,593 --> 00:30:45,094
Really? No kidding!

403
00:30:45,802 --> 00:30:46,804
Not a single hit.

404
00:30:46,971 --> 00:30:47,805
Not one.

405
00:30:49,891 --> 00:30:51,142
I don't give a damn.

406
00:30:51,308 --> 00:30:53,894
What I love doing
is singing, expressing myself.

407
00:30:54,061 --> 00:30:55,395
Not selling records.

408
00:30:55,563 --> 00:30:58,441
Sure, you have to stay free.

409
00:30:59,025 --> 00:31:00,692
Exactly. Look at me!

410
00:31:01,318 --> 00:31:03,238
How about this for freedom!

411
00:31:04,071 --> 00:31:06,532
All this time,
did I ever ask for a favor?

412
00:31:06,865 --> 00:31:08,451
Except the 3,000-euro loan.

413
00:31:08,617 --> 00:31:11,203
Besides money. Let's elevate the debate.

414
00:31:11,954 --> 00:31:13,623
I mean, a favor for a friend.

415
00:31:14,082 --> 00:31:15,959
The poor guy has nothing in his life.

416
00:31:16,125 --> 00:31:18,877
Home, the pool. The pool, home.

417
00:31:19,461 --> 00:31:21,130
He needs to get laid.

418
00:31:21,297 --> 00:31:24,174
I doubt he ever got laid in his life.

419
00:31:24,424 --> 00:31:25,343
Sure, I did.

420
00:31:25,843 --> 00:31:27,010
I've done it.

421
00:31:27,428 --> 00:31:28,637
I made love.

422
00:31:28,805 --> 00:31:30,765
Leave this to me, will you?

423
00:31:31,516 --> 00:31:32,767
You bang me, right?

424
00:31:32,933 --> 00:31:35,603
- So bang him. Same difference!
- Totally not.

425
00:31:36,436 --> 00:31:39,065
Marcus, let it go.
I don't think she wants to.

426
00:31:39,231 --> 00:31:40,441
No, she doesn't.

427
00:31:40,607 --> 00:31:41,901
Let it go.

428
00:31:42,067 --> 00:31:43,944
No, don't let it go, you jerk!

429
00:31:46,823 --> 00:31:47,781
Did I upset you?

430
00:31:47,949 --> 00:31:49,200
Guys, let's go.

431
00:31:50,076 --> 00:31:50,701
Great job.

432
00:31:51,286 --> 00:31:53,246
Pay up. I forgot my wallet.

433
00:31:54,247 --> 00:31:55,873
You often forget it.

434
00:31:57,083 --> 00:31:59,794
I'll pay you back tomorrow.
Here's the thing...

435
00:32:00,336 --> 00:32:02,630
You won't get laid being a tightwad.

436
00:32:02,797 --> 00:32:04,673
Women detest a tightwad.

437
00:32:05,048 --> 00:32:07,343
Black mark for you
but I've got your back.

438
00:32:07,509 --> 00:32:08,176
Wait!

439
00:32:08,469 --> 00:32:10,555
No, my friend's buying.

440
00:32:11,597 --> 00:32:12,557
Mr. Marcus!

441
00:32:13,057 --> 00:32:13,766
What?

442
00:32:13,932 --> 00:32:16,728
Sorry to bother you,
but we need to talk.

443
00:32:17,936 --> 00:32:19,146
Duty calls, sorry.

444
00:32:19,355 --> 00:32:20,940
I'm the boss, the CEO.

445
00:32:22,733 --> 00:32:25,653
Have fun.
That button there changes the colors.

446
00:32:27,779 --> 00:32:29,198
This can't go on.

447
00:32:29,365 --> 00:32:30,115
What can't?

448
00:32:30,282 --> 00:32:32,868
I told you 4 months ago.
Nothing happened.

449
00:32:33,076 --> 00:32:35,413
Something has to give.
We owe 150,000

450
00:32:35,622 --> 00:32:36,873
to our suppliers.

451
00:32:37,832 --> 00:32:40,000
And no income to cover loans.

452
00:32:40,876 --> 00:32:41,961
I'll get by.

453
00:32:42,377 --> 00:32:45,589
You don't get it.
We'll be bankrupt before Xmas.

454
00:32:48,759 --> 00:32:49,885
Before Xmas?

455
00:32:51,304 --> 00:32:53,681
- You're sure of the math?
- Sure.

456
00:32:57,434 --> 00:32:59,519
Call her a cab, will you, please?

457
00:33:04,150 --> 00:33:05,233
Hello.

458
00:33:06,277 --> 00:33:08,820
My name's Delphine. I'm an alcoholic.

459
00:33:09,071 --> 00:33:11,449
I've been sober five years now.

460
00:33:12,075 --> 00:33:14,701
It started when I was 26.

461
00:33:15,702 --> 00:33:19,624
I was doing
artistic swimming in duet.

462
00:33:21,541 --> 00:33:24,836
It was international level,
competing in championships.

463
00:33:25,003 --> 00:33:26,381
And I won a lot of them.

464
00:33:26,547 --> 00:33:28,799
We won a lot, my partner and I.

465
00:33:29,759 --> 00:33:32,720
For me,
those were the best years of my life.

466
00:33:32,886 --> 00:33:36,348
It was a wonderful time. Awesome.

467
00:33:37,016 --> 00:33:38,226
And then...

468
00:33:39,143 --> 00:33:41,561
Then came a major incident.

469
00:33:42,771 --> 00:33:46,733
She was forced
to give up swimming with me.

470
00:33:46,901 --> 00:33:48,568
To give up swimming, period.

471
00:33:49,153 --> 00:33:50,363
Likewise for me.

472
00:33:50,529 --> 00:33:53,156
My whole career had been with her.

473
00:33:53,324 --> 00:33:55,867
Without her, it just wasn't right.

474
00:33:56,786 --> 00:33:58,078
I think I...

475
00:33:58,246 --> 00:34:00,707
I should've been there for her then.

476
00:34:02,458 --> 00:34:06,712
Instead, I blamed her
for us being forced to quit.

477
00:34:08,005 --> 00:34:10,340
Now I have only myself to blame.

478
00:34:10,717 --> 00:34:13,802
Back then,
competition, the pool and stuff.

479
00:34:13,969 --> 00:34:15,722
It left a hole in my life.

480
00:34:16,054 --> 00:34:17,056
She...

481
00:34:17,681 --> 00:34:19,141
left a hole in my life.

482
00:34:21,393 --> 00:34:22,728
I was broken.

483
00:34:23,730 --> 00:34:25,063
I couldn't see...

484
00:34:26,231 --> 00:34:28,608
I was just surviving until the first,

485
00:34:28,818 --> 00:34:30,820
you guessed it, gin and tonic.

486
00:34:31,653 --> 00:34:34,489
I had never drunk alcohol.
It was my first time.

487
00:34:34,657 --> 00:34:37,034
You can imagine what happened next.

488
00:34:37,702 --> 00:34:39,119
Just falling.

489
00:34:40,454 --> 00:34:43,081
I thought about ending it all.

490
00:34:44,416 --> 00:34:45,543
What saved me

491
00:34:46,085 --> 00:34:49,005
was, on the one hand, my team

492
00:34:49,172 --> 00:34:51,257
of male synchronized swimmers.

493
00:34:51,882 --> 00:34:56,137
Yes, I coach a team
with serious potential.

494
00:34:56,304 --> 00:34:58,972
But what really hauled me
out of deep shooot...

495
00:35:02,726 --> 00:35:04,144
As lame as it sounds...

496
00:35:05,103 --> 00:35:06,856
It could be a line

497
00:35:07,023 --> 00:35:08,690
from music in a supermarket...

498
00:35:09,233 --> 00:35:10,318
Was love.

499
00:35:12,527 --> 00:35:15,489
Saying it now, I could slap myself,
but it's true.

500
00:35:17,699 --> 00:35:19,076
He saved my life.

501
00:35:28,376 --> 00:35:31,213
Hi Serge, this is Bertrand,
our new hire.

502
00:35:31,922 --> 00:35:32,965
Show him the ropes.

503
00:35:33,673 --> 00:35:37,177
I won't put you here
until you're up to speed.

504
00:35:37,344 --> 00:35:38,846
Morning, ma'am. Excellent choice.

505
00:35:39,222 --> 00:35:40,972
Hey, guys, break over!

506
00:35:41,932 --> 00:35:43,976
Here, we have the high-end models.

507
00:35:46,144 --> 00:35:48,356
This is the cafeteria-slash-break room.

508
00:35:48,523 --> 00:35:50,983
Staff come here for coffee and stuff.

509
00:35:51,150 --> 00:35:53,318
What's going on here?

510
00:35:55,278 --> 00:35:56,530
Your uniform.

511
00:36:02,494 --> 00:36:04,996
We have a Bertrand with great sales.
I can't...

512
00:36:05,164 --> 00:36:05,998
See?

513
00:36:06,289 --> 00:36:08,960
Welcome. See you in convertibles
for a briefing.

514
00:36:09,585 --> 00:36:10,878
Convertibles?

515
00:36:11,795 --> 00:36:12,672
Sofas.

516
00:36:13,088 --> 00:36:14,882
This is a furniture store.

517
00:36:15,048 --> 00:36:16,800
It's gotta go faster up there.

518
00:36:17,425 --> 00:36:18,385
See you later.

519
00:36:21,054 --> 00:36:24,016
- You thought it over?
- I'm not quite sure but yes.

520
00:36:24,224 --> 00:36:25,268
Thought what over?

521
00:36:25,434 --> 00:36:27,561
- His foreign language option.
- And?

522
00:36:28,311 --> 00:36:29,063
I think

523
00:36:29,771 --> 00:36:31,731
I'll go for Spanish.

524
00:36:32,108 --> 00:36:33,067
Spanish?

525
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:34,985
You think or you're sure?

526
00:36:35,527 --> 00:36:37,070
Sure, I guess.

527
00:36:37,780 --> 00:36:39,239
Spanish gets you nowhere.

528
00:36:39,407 --> 00:36:41,909
- Spanish gets you nowhere?
- Nowhere.

529
00:36:42,909 --> 00:36:44,452
Why take Spanish?

530
00:36:46,246 --> 00:36:47,414
Our roots.

531
00:36:47,956 --> 00:36:49,750
I mean, yours and granny's.

532
00:36:51,126 --> 00:36:51,918
Who said that?

533
00:36:52,085 --> 00:36:53,170
You said that?

534
00:36:54,130 --> 00:36:55,338
About my mother?

535
00:36:55,840 --> 00:36:56,965
Why talk about her?

536
00:36:57,550 --> 00:36:58,925
Dad, please. Calm down.

537
00:36:59,092 --> 00:37:00,552
Are you stupid or what?

538
00:37:00,719 --> 00:37:02,429
Why stir up all that shooot?

539
00:37:02,597 --> 00:37:03,431
